name: Triangular.js
body:
## What's that you say? _Three-way_ data binding?
Form data seamlessly synced between your JavaScript, the DOM, and LocalStorage.

Oh yeah, that means _it syncs across browser tabs._ Yes, really.

## Even works on Grandpa's old IE7.
triangular.js should work for IE7+. Of course, the _real_ browsers are supported, too.
note: Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration.
